WSISD will RETURN to school Wednesday, September 2nd on our regular schedule.

Buses will run at the regular times.

Remote learners may face some challenges with access to teachers depending our internet connectivity (currently down in our district).

Students unable to return due to evacuation will have excused absences. Parents will need to contact the campus to report the absences.

****Reminder, Friday is an EARLY RELEASE DAY!

Passes for the game against High Island will be available for pick up at the Admin office on Thursday. First come, first served. Limit two per person. All Football players and Cheerleaders will receive two Passes for their parents/guardians.

Call Admin to reserve your Pass or to be added to the wait-list. PASSES MUST BE PRESENTED AT THE GATE TO PURCHASE YOUR ENTRY TICKET. Due to COVID, space is limited to 50% and those without passes will not be allowed entry.

#TigerStrong
Go Tigers!!

Respectfully,
Cristal

08/24/20 10PM UPDATE FROM NATIONAL
HURRICANE CENTER.

Sabine county has NOT been listed as a declared disaster area, however, A TROPICAL STORM WATCH IS IN EFFECT FOR JASPER COUNTY.

HURRICANE WATCH NOW IN EFFECT FROM PORT BOLIVAR, TEXAS TO WEST OF MORGAN CITY, LOUISIANA.

Marco has been downgraded to a tropical depression and is no longer a factor.

AS EXPECTED, LAURAâ€™S TRACK HAS SHIFTED A BIT TO THE WEST. The rainfall is still a factor concerning for our area.

Laura is expected to make landfall early Thursday morning.

The intensity of the storm is going expected to INCREASE IN STRENGTH. Predictions are 100+ mph winds in the Jasper area early Thursday morning.

Next update expected will be around 4am.

We continue to watch the forecasts and plan with local agencies.

West Sabine High School
West Sabine Elementary School

We are excited to announce that West Sabine ISD has received a grant in the amount of $119,000 awarded for supporting the SRA Reading Program ($19,000 @WestSabineElementary) and the purchase of technology ($90,000) and purchase of connectivity devices for our students ($10,000).

This Grant is made in accordance with the Thomas T. Keeler Grant Program, and in honor of Thomas T. Keeler and his wife, Cora T. Keeler; and in memory of his grandfather, T.L.L. Temple; and his mother Marguerite Temple Payne. We are very appreciative of the philanthropic support from the Temple Family and Keeler Grant Program.

We are also very a thankful for the support of the Pineland Service Club for their outreach on behalf of WSISD!

Sabine County Reporter

As the technology director for West Sabine ISD during these challenging times, it is amazing to see how we can all come together to accomplish great things. Tonight was another great example as we used Zoom for our board meeting. We're adapting to continue to take care of our students, teachers and staff. While we may not be able to be together physically, with the use of technology, we can still serve our community in the best way we can.

I cannot thank our board enough for entrusting in the use of technology to serve our community.

Sincerely,
Daniel Havard

post_text:
Good Evening Parents and Students:
It is with regret that I inform everyone that our High School Prom is cancelled for Saturday, March 21st. This is a very difficult decision and one that is unavoidable at this time. Our plans are to reschedule the Prom for a later date once we have more certainty about the coming weeks and what impact COVID 19 has in our state and geographical area. We will continue to pay close attention to Center for Disease Control updates in the coming days. I am very sorry because I know this is a long awaited event for our students as we were all looking forward to Saturday. Please feel free to call my office if you have questions at 584.2655 or you may reach anyone on Prom Committee at the high school (contact Mrs. Jessica Wallace)

COLLEEN CONN IS NEW PRINCIPAL AT WSHS

Colleen (Rueffer) Conn has been named new principal of West Sabine High School. A unanimous vote to approve Mrs. Conn was recorded by the board at its meeting Monday, July 15, 2019.

Having most recently lived in Whitehouse, Mrs. Conn is a former longtime Sabine County resident and graduated from Hemphill High School.

Mrs. Conn will begin her duties immediately as West Sabine is preparing to begin its 2019-2020 school year.

post_text:
The community of Pineland/West Sabine ISD has suffered a tremendous loss due to a car accident on Hwy 184 yesterday afternoon. We are deeply saddened that Easton Horn, a West Sabine High School student has passed away. Easton's mother was also killed in the accident. We extend our heartfelt condolences to the family. Additionally another West Sabine student was injured in the accident along with a child from a neighboring district. Our prayers go out to each of these families as they deal with loss and healing from injuries.

Our entire school district is saddened by this event. It is very difficult to experience the death of a young person. The West Sabine High School campus will be open on Monday for students to drop by and speak to a counselor as needed. The well being of our students will remain a top priority as we deal with the emotions surrounding this tragedy.

Jane B. Stephenson, Interim Superintendent
